	&lt;p&gt;Mike was an awesome .NET developer and writer (and also wrote one of the most popular &lt;a href="http://larkware.com/"&gt;.NET news blogs&lt;/a&gt; ); nowadays he’s an awesome Rails developer and writer.&lt;/p&gt;


	&lt;p&gt;In our small-but-growing convoy of those who’ve made the transition from .NET to Rails, Mike has been a true pioneer.&lt;/p&gt;


	&lt;p&gt;Whether you originally hail from Microsoft development land (like I do) or not, I highly recommend his &lt;a href="http://www.afreshcup.com/"&gt;notes on all things Ruby, Rails, and beyond&lt;/a&gt; .&lt;/p&gt;
          
